## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="e7a3b-102">El <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioStateChangedEventArgs.AudioState%2A> propiedad obtiene una nueva instancia de la <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioState> enumeración cuando un <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.AudioStateChanged?displayProperty=nameWithType> o un <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.AudioStateChanged?displayProperty=nameWithType> provoca el evento.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e7a3b-102">The <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioStateChangedEventArgs.AudioState%2A> property gets a new instance of the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.AudioState> enumeration when a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.AudioStateChanged?displayProperty=nameWithType> or a <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer.AudioStateChanged?displayProperty=nameWithType> event is raised.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="e7a3b-103">Puede obtener el estado actual del audio de entrada mediante el `AudioState` propiedad de la <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> o <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> clases.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e7a3b-103">You can obtain the current state of the audio input using the `AudioState` property of the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognizer> or <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine> classes.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="e7a3b-104">El ejemplo siguiente muestra un controlador de eventos para controlar el estado cambiante de audio de un motor de reconocimiento de voz.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="e7a3b-104">The following example demonstrates an event handler for handling the changing audio state of a speech recognition engine.</span></span>  
  
```csharp  
  
private SpeechRecognitionEngine sre;  
  
// Initialize the SpeechRecognitionEngine object.   
private void Initialize()  
{  
  sre = new SpeechRecognitionEngine();  
  
  // Add a handler for the AudioStateChanged event.  
  sre.AudioStateChanged += new EventHandler<AudioStateChangedEventArgs>(sre_AudioStateChanged);  
  
  // Add other initialization code here.  
}  
  
// Handle the AudioStateChanged event.   
void sre_AudioStateChanged(object sender, AudioStateChangedEventArgs e)  
{  
  AudioState newState = e.AudioState;  
  
  // Handle event here.  
}  
  
```
